Project Stage - II (Data Modeling)

Goals
	The goal of Stage II is to develop the data for modeling and comparative analysis.That is comparing US with other countries on number of COVID cases and deaths. County based information for different states in the US is also analysed. Since COVID dataset is huge, this analysis is focussed on selected dates, starting from 2020, July - 2020, December.

Tasks:

	- Compare the weekly statistics (mean, median, mode) for number of cases and deaths across US.
	- Compare the data against other countries of the world. Data Source: https://ourworldindata.org/coronavirus-source-data
	- Compare atleast 5 countries with 5 similar populations.
	- Plot weekly trends (cases and deaths) of US and compare other countries. Utilize aggregrate, normalized by population, difference in cases, and log normalized values. (hint: do normalization: number of cases per 100,000, and then use np.log10())
	- Identify the peak weeks of the cases and deaths in US and other countries. Background research to see the reasoning for the peaks during certain period of time like holidays, vacations, travel, weather, etc. Explain with a description in the notebooks.
